caption: We had dinner on Saturday night 3 20 21. Our server was Brian, our party included a 4 year old, a 2 year old and 2 adults who are vegans. Brian went well beyond the call of duty to accommodate the vegans making several trips to our table to suggest various dishes he could provide before coming up with a veggie pasta and salad. He was wonderful with the kids also. The food at Filuppo's is always outstanding as is the service, however Brian took it to another level that night. You are missing a great treat if you haven't been here yet.
Best Italian food around 😋
My wife and I enjoyed our wonderfull meal. The paneed chicken already was great but the veal Marsala my wife ordered was better.
Excellent veal marsala.
Our first time here.  Delicious meal. Excellent service.  We will definitely be back. Chicken marsala and veal parm were just perfect.  Gil was our waiter and he was the best!
We love the friendly staff, the food is great and the atmosphere is welcoming. We love to listen to the Italian songs they play softly in the background. Always a good meal and good time.

As always my daughter and I dined at Phillippo’s The food was spectacular as the presentation was also. Our waiter Brian along with the team of waiters worked great together.Thank You Phillippo’s for a wonderful night out. Michael and Alexis Cascio
Yay
Excellent
I highly recommend Ristorante Filippo for dinner.  It doesn't get any better than this. Great food, service and atmosphere.  Johnathan was the best !!!

Hey guys this is a great spot to bring the wife or girlfriend for a nice dinner out. It's a small restaurant but very comfortable. Food is top notch. Only gave 4 stars because there better places , but this one is really good. Good food good drinks and wine. Go and enjoy.
Love this place, good food, good service.
This is a true hidden gem in the most genuine essence of both words!
Very cozy and delicious dishes.Friendly staff..

I’ve eaten here twice, once for pasta, once for steak, and the food is very good.  The quality is worthy of four stars relative to the price, but at $52 for a ribeye, the quality doesn’t rate 5 stars.  Also, my wife ordered a filet, but they brought her a ribeye. I rated it down one more because we took our three kids and I asked them to split an adult meal (spaghetti and meatballs) between two of them (ages 5 and 7). My eldest, 9, ordered an adult meal for himself, shrimp pasta and soup. They said they wouldn’t split the spaghetti, but could bring an extra plate.  They forgot the extra plate. We reminded them about it. They never brought it. We used the bread plate. Then when reviewing the bill I saw the charged $7 for the extra plate we never got. I didn’t ask them to fix it as it was a $250 bill and I usually leave 20%, so I just subtracted the extra plate charge from the tip. Anyway, won’t return a third time.
Food, atmosphere and service was fantastic!! I highly recommend this place!

This is a quaint italian restaurant located within walking distance of the Sheraton Galleria and the Courtyard Galleria. Due to the times, there was a lengthy wait which was offset by the quality of the food. They have a wide variety of wine but very limited supply/variety of beer. It could be five stars but it was a bit slow and for an Italian restaurant not to have Italian beer made my decision a four star
We had a great meal and the service was fantastic.
Not impressed with the food, considering the price we paid. The wait staff was very nice, only positive thing I can say!

Really good food.
Wonderful food. Astonishing service. Fantastic experience
I had the chicken parmesan... It was amazing. Very good! Great deserts too.
Very expensive. I ordered lasagna as a “special.” I was totally blind sided when the bill arrived. It was very mediocre for $23.  The only positive was the cocktails were strong. Won’t be back.
Service spotty. Felt rushed even though there was no one waiting..several menu items unavailable..food mediocre. If you want Italian there are many better places to eat here in town.
It's our go to place for special occasions, even if the special occasion is 'just' dinner.  Had the NOLA style BBQ shrimp.  Simply amazing.  Seasoned perfectly.
As always....fantastic. Tonight, they saved our night out.
Had the trout meuniere amandine. It was the very best I have enjoyed in a long time! Kudos to the chef.
Delicious. We did not have a reservation but they were able to fit us right in. I had the chicken picata over sauteed spinach.
Small place with Gigantic unbelievable tasting food. Great quite atmosphere where you can actually hear yourself think. Fantastic wait staff.
Food is fabulous best Italian food in the City of New Orleans

Food was delicious! Service was ok. The scenery is a little outdated and could use some freshening up. We had a reservation for 8:45 and didn't get seated til after 9 even when there were tables available. It was Valentine's day so maybe they were just under pressure. I would give it another go on a normal night. I also ordered a Bloody Mary and it was of the worst I ever had.

Food was average @ best. The caesar salad was drenched in dressing and the sauce on both entrees (Pollo Picatta/Gamberi Gagliano) was watery. The hostess/servers were very friendly.
Was an amazing visit,  15 of us went and had a wonderful time.  The food was great service was awesome.   Many of our group eat there regularly.

The interior and exterior of this small, stand-alone property reflect its 18-year-old age. The owner & assistant were friendly and quick. I ordered the Pasta & Meatballs, which was served with fresh-baked bread & butter. The portions were large and good. I would recommend it and return. RJT
I just had the BEST Italian food ever. The cozy and warm atmosphere is such a sweet little relaxing restaurant  I highly recommend it to all. Very reasonable

I travel all over the world from the UK for business and this has to be the worse excuse for an Italian I have ever experienced bland tasting , initially the waitress who served us was unhelpful and unpleasant the waiter was better but didn’t feel welcome. I wouldn’t bother wasting your money other local places that are much better.

Great good and excellent service

(Translated by Google) Congratulations to the chef and his team! Being Italian, I finally ate in a real Italian restaurant! Tired of American restaurants claiming to make two Italian dishes to say they are Italian. A big thank you to them for raising the level against these American impostors!  (Original) Congratulazioni allo chef e alla sua squadra !  Essendo italiano, ho finalmente mangiato in un vero ristorante italiano ! Stanco di ristoranti americani che affermano di fare due piatti italiani dire che sono italiani. Un grande grazie a loro per aver innalzato il livello contro questi impostori americani !

(Translated by Google) Well done to the chef for his great food, but why put cinnamon in the cannoli? 🥴  (Original) Bravo au chef pour son excellente cuisine, mais pourquoi mettre de la cannelle dans les cannolis ? 🥴
Great
Excellent shrimp scampi!

Excellent service. The food was wonderful. Everything was made to order, with the exception of the red sauce which is made in bulk, according to our waiter. The restaurant is small, but very cozy. We had the eggplant medallions, veal marsala, and veal alfredo - they were all great. My husband, who normally doesn't like a red sauce, loved theirs. That says a lot!  Will definitely be back!

This may be the worst service I have experienced in many years. A very small restaurant with numerous and since we we not regulars we were treated terribly. Even to walking out with the desert that I ordered to go. Wish there was something below zero for this place. STAY AWAY AT ALL COST!
Excellent little quiet place.  Food was very good.

I ordered the fish with crawfish sauce. The fish was old and the sauce was watery and tasteless. The eggplant parmesan would have been good if they seasoned it. Oh and the parking is VERY limited. Won't be returning.
Great food, hidden gem

A classic Italian restaurant tucked inside of an old house in a residential neighborhood oh, it has a very neat down home kind of feel to it. The food is good quality and the prices are upscale as is the service. Unfortunately I think this place suffers from the same condition most Italian restaurants that claim to be upscale in the region have, their food is not bad but it's really not distinctive either. The ingredients don't seem as fresh as really good Italian food should be imo. For the prices they charge, is disappointing that they also try to upsell you on extra things to top your entree with. All Things Considered, this place is consistently among the better Italian places in the area.
Went there a while back... The fried calamari was tasty but the waitress, Meridith, was disgusting..... Smelled like she hadn't showered in a week.... Liked the mafia music though
The wait staff is very attentive to their diners, the portions were larger than most restaurants, and the food was delicious.

My favorite Italian restaurant in the New Orleans area. The eggplant medallions were delicious and I don't really care for eggplant. The shrimp appetizer with olive oil and garlic was delish. Their red gravy was a tad bit sweet to me but delicious. Everyone else at the table absolutely loved their entrees (Trout Almondine, Veal Marsala, Veal Picatta and an Alfredo dish) all saying can it was the best they've ever had. The Tiramisu was excellent. Their bread pudding was OMG! You could really taste the cinnamon but it wasn't overwhelming. We had to wait for a bit for our entrees but so worth the wait. Oh, I forgot. The coffee was really good, too.

This place is family owned and operated. The owners are very personable and lovely. Unfortunately my fiance and I went on a very unexpected busy night for them. They said it was the second busiest day since Thanksgiving and they were not expecting such a large crowd. It was our first experience and we waited at our table for 3 hours for our food. They were so apologetic that they gave us free drinks and cannoli. And in all honesty after we waited there for 3 hours they should have comped our dinners. We decided to take our food home to go to eat due to the fact that it was so late. But I have to admit it is the best Italian food I have ever eaten. I will not allow this strange occurrence stop me fro giving them another chance. It's a little piece of Italy sitting right smack in the middle of Metairie. Kudos to the chef.
Solid Italian ...everything from Fish to Veal

Everything was wonderful.  Quite possibly the best Chicken Marsala, Spaghetti and meatballs we've ever eaten. We also loved the cozy, quaint atmosphere.  the owners and staff were amazing! Recommend to everyone! You won't be disappointed!  Wayne and Lori, West Monroe
Always good food. Directions on GPS confusing but will eventually gets you there. Nice cosy romantic getaway.
great food
Went a year ago during Mardi Gras and the owner was amazing. So many great tips on the parades and my meal was to die for! I can't wait to go back this year.
Delicious!
Can't say enough about the owner. There was a mix up in our reservation on a busy night and she did everything she could to accommodate our large party. Very good experience.
Excellent food and great service. Great atmosphere.  We had a party of 13 reserved and service was prompt and sincere.
Christmas work luncheon. Absolutely delicioso.
Fantastic!!! Fresh first class ingredients cooked to bring out great flavors. Teriffic service.
Excellent!!!! The food and the staff are amazing, hands down!!!!

Great service and food. Our appetizer of crab claws in a buttery garlic wine sauce which I would definitely recommend, lasagna that my husband loved, veal picatta which was so good, and we tried the tiramisu and the best bread pudding. We had leftovers of everything because the portions were gigantic.
Haven't been since I was a kid. Was better than I remembered.  Veal was incredibly tender.  Everything was amazing, service and overall experience....
Without a doubt some of the best food and dining experiences in town. Great service too!!
Great food and generous portions at a reasonable price. Service was excellent too. A great experience.
Best Italian food around!!!   Great service  will definitely be back.
Great food. And even better staff
I have mixed reviews on this place. The food was good but the bar was really slow at getting the drinks out.

The food is delicious
wonderful,  second time around and haven't disappointed . AMAZING,  I will return return again
Great service good food
Food was delicious. Service was good. Portions were huge.

I loved it!!,😉 it's an Eclectic blend of Greek and Italian dishes and ironically some of the management has Hispanic /Central American background. I I think one of the appetizers that evening had more of a Central American flavor to it I thought prices were very reasonable and the staff was unbelievably friendly and attentive. There's a flaming cheese dish that is brought to your table-- still flaming!!- that I'd highly enjoyed Great for a date or family dining.  It's in a sort of strip mall with safe, free parking but don't let it fool you.... inside is really nice! If I'm ever back in Virginia I would definitely pay them a visit!
Veal is phenomenal with the homemade marinara sauce
Fantastic! The best veal parmesan I've ever had in my life. I would go here to impress somebody that I was with to show them how good I am at picking out restaurants.
Cozy and elegant, reminiscent of pre Katrina fine dining in the metro Nola area. Unbelievably fresh ingredients, top notch service, fully stocked bar. Excellent experience overall!
Food is delicious- more than we could have eat- and the staff is fabulous!  Definitely recommended!
Per usual. Phillip and staff were at their very best
Excellent food. Neat atmosphere and great service.
Great service, the food was delicious. Definitely going to return. Tiramisu was outstanding.

The veal steak special was amazing.  I have  even here a few times and have never had anything that wasn't delicious although the tomahawk veal steak was hands down my favorite so far.  I will be back!

Intimate surroundings, casual atmosphere, over the top quality in Italian food!  I had the house-made lasagna. I consider myself a sort of lasagna connoisseur, trying it wherever I can. Most of the time, I leave the restaurant disappointed. Not this time. Hands down, this is the finest slice of lasagna I have ever eaten. The chef pays attention to the smallest details, with layer after layer of perfectly done lasagna noodles interspersed with incredible cheeses, meats, herbs, and, out of nowhere, the thinnest slice of eggplant.  Yep, eggplant.  If I didn't tell you, you would have never guessed.  I talked two in my party into getting it. Both were entirely delighted. All of us took home substantial portions.  So it goes without saying (but I'll say it anyway), the portions are HUGE.  The quality outstanding.  The service is perfect, almost appearing out of thin air with a refreshed glass is whatever you were drinking.  I have eaten here in small groups and with a party of 18. I am never disappointed.
Small restaurant, BIG FLAVOR!!
Excellent food but pricey.
Great Food
The food here is very good. The trout with tosted almonds was very delicious.
Great! Heading there again
Authentic Italian, great menu, servers were great too!
I pick up my orders, so can't comment on the wait staff.  Good food though.
The food was very good. The atmosphere was cozy and comfortable. The staff was attentive without over doing it.
Must visit!!
Excellent lasagna!

I've never heard of this place
Awesome presentations! Delectable food!!!

Excellent meal and “neighborhood” atmosphere and service. One area for improvement is the wine list. There are opportunities for improvement that would elevate the list to the level of the food while maintaining the current price points.

Group of 8. The trout special & panneed veal we're all overcooked & dry. Alfredo sauce had no taste. Only one salad dressing - house vinegarette that was too sweet & so full of black pepper we all were coughing.  There are so many better local restaurants.
So delicious.  Great service.  Drinks,  food.  Amazing

Outstanding dinner! Our server Sue and Chef/Owner Philip made it a great evening!

Excellent! Quaint. Great date venue

Service and restaurant tried to appear upscale but failed. Very small place. Food was prepared and presented well. It was good but over-priced. Wine was served by half glass but charged full price and it too was over-priced for being the house wine.
Food and service were both good and enjoyable.
Top 5 Italian restaurant....cozy romantic Italian restaurant....loved the calamari  and the entire meal....Chef came out to talk with us too...enjoy
I absolutely Love this place.  Food is always delicious.
Great food and atmosphere
Been multiple times over many years and never had a bad experience. If he ever has the eggplant topped with lobster, do yourself a favor and order it. I dream about this dish on a regular basis.
Best of Metairie. Hell Best of New Orleans
The pork chop was amazing nice and friendly atmosphere and the wine selection was authentic

My Girlfriend Pat and I had dinner there last Valentines Day. We Enjoyed our experience there and plan to return this Tuesday for Valentine's day again.  For us it was just right. The Atmosphere was Quaint and just Intimate enough.
I like this place. the food is very good. I will come back to this place.

My husband and I had reservations, they sat us in a cramped corner table. It was freezing inside the dining room. There was a comfortable empty next to us that remained open the entire night???(why weren't we seated there?!) We were never told about the specials of the night, which we would have ordered had we known. The house cab. is like water. The red sauce was flavorless and  watery. I'm sorry we wasted a night out together to have such a terrible experience. Save your money, I promise you can cook a better meal at home.
Best Italian food I've had in NOLA. If you like a sweet red sauce (which I do) you will fall in love with their lasagna. I did. BTW, H-U-G-E portions.

Amazing experience! The owner, Phil, came and talked to us for at least five minutes, and the waitress, Sue, was attentive, warm and funny. The food, from appetizer to dessert, was absolutely amazing, and the atmosphere was warm and inviting. Probably my favorite Italian restaurant in the city now! Highly recommended.
Amazing food, fantastic atmosphere, stellar service!
Staff was exceptional. Pretty much anything you order you will love.
The meal was delicious! The best crab claw appetizer ever!! The service was wonderful also. We will definitely come back when we are in the area!
Remarkable a hidden jewel. I was invited to dine there yesterday for the first time. And I will be going back again today.

I was staying at a hotel down the street and decided to give this place a try. I ordered the chicken Parmesan (which is my favorite Italian dish that I order everywhere) and it tasted like it could have been good.... aside from the red sauce. It had a really strange sweet taste to it. It definitely wasn't your traditional Italian red sauce and unfortunately, it threw off the whole dish for me. The marinara dipping sauce that came with the calamari had the same sweet taste. I wasn't a huge fan.

I always sort of thought a grilled chicken salad was something to be quietly endured, rather than enjoyed. Yours was delicious. The chicken was good. It wasn't rubbery. That alone baffles all my preconceptions. I was with three other people and they all had great dishes as well. Wonderful, and a nice young waiter, Ben? I think? Lavish praise on all your youngish male waiters in case I got the wrong name. Thank you, and I'll be back.
Great food for a darn good price. Service is excellent as well. The atmosphere is cozy and romantic. My wife and I love going here for food.
Caesar salad was the best I ever had. Good great and service was outstanding.
Took family out. great food, house dressing was really good but would have liked more than just lettuce.  great service.

Wow!!! I can not express in words the complete enjoyment that my husband and I shared in the food and ambiance here at Pillippo's tonight. How many years have I wasted finding total satisfaction in a 1st class Italian cuisine Restaurant. Look no further, it is here. Everything you desire and more. How many of you have been looking for the local Italian flavor of the highest quality? Look no more. This is my favorite by far and will share this best kept secret with my family and friends from now on. Thank you very much and we will be a regular in your most special establishment for years to come. This is a place where memories are made. =)

My boyfriend and I just moved to Metairie and lived very close to the restaurant. We decided to check it out. We were very impressed with the food and the atmosphere. As we were sitting and eating, we noticed that people kept walking in and saying hello to the staff like old friends. After we introduced ourselves to who turned out to be the owner and felt very welcomed into the community. Definitely recommend the food and the whole experience!

Very good,always! Need to change the specials. The lasagna is the best !!! Shrimp a la vodka is the best !! Unfortunately both dishes are not on the menu most of the time.  It should be the nightly special rather than the trout almondine that I took once and I won't take again, it is just not Italian  enough and really not special . There eggplant dish  and appetizer  are delicious. Their salad with crab meat is delicious. Need to make lasagna...... it is an expected dish in an Italian restaurant :) I will go many times again ... just make few little upgrades please.
The meal from salad to trout almond in was wonderful,  as was my husband's pasta marinara
Food was excellent  service was professional and friendly owner is the Chef  he made sure our food and service was excellent

The food is alway phenomenal.  Eggplant to die for.  My family and I eat there at least 4 to 6 times a month.  You can't get a better italian meal locally.  Each plate is definitely made with love. Just wish they delivered for lunch.

An employee of mine recomended this place. My wife and I had Lunch there, she had a crabmeat salad and trout stuffed with crabmeat, I had the porkchop, believe me, this place is way over rated. The bill was a little under $100.00. The food and service  was nothing to write home about for what we paid. I know I will not be going back to Ristorante Filippo again even if the prices goes down. I was thinking that the great reviews that u read  were written by the owner himself. If you want a good meal for a great price go to the come back inn on west metaire, the food is much better and at a fraction of the cost..I eat there at least 2 or 3 times a week and I have no ownership whatsoever, try it...
